We love the way that B.B. for Reschio has evolved and has come of age with its own Instagram account @bbforreschio and now a dedicated website too: bbforreschio.com
As an award-winning architect, Benedikt Bolza has designed and restructured houses, industrial premises and our very own 36-room Hotel Castello di Reschio. He has let nature dictate while creating extensive landscapes and gardens around the houses. With each project, his hand drawn bespoke pieces have been realised by local artisans. Lighting, furniture and accessories, all beautiful objects that hark back to a glamorous age, yet immensely practical in today’s world. Frequently an item will pass between several artisans, each specialising in a different aspect such as interlacing webbing beneath a chair, angling the welder’s torch, carving out marble for a basin, hand-stitching a lampshade or patinating a bronze coffee table. Every item made is directly connected to the designer and is
handcrafted for a specific order. It is packed in custom-made crates to embark upon its final journey, branded with the B.B. for Reschio logo featuring the Tabaccaia, Reschio’s creative hub - the place where the first innovative sparks were ignited.
Our creative team had enormous fun making the launch video... prepare to be amused, scroll back and click to play

Conte Antonio Bolza, a devoted horseman, established a stud of purebred Andalusians in 1999. Together with Antonello Radicchi they travelled through Spain in search of the perfect stallion, when they reached Seville, it was an eureka moment as Uranio VI was led out. His progeny now numbers forty with names such as Il Magnifico, Aurora and Serenissimo demonstrating the utter joy of those early foals born at Reschio. Four or five foals are bred each year and the young stock is trained gently by Antonello using only a head collar.
 
The loving care that is devoted to these magical animals cannot be underestimated. Galloping free in the rolling meadows of Reschio, their phenomenal stables, with panoramic views of the Niccone Valley were designed and built by Conte Benedikt. So luxurious are the Scuderie and manèage that humans use the space for celebrations, should the horses allow.
 
Summer residents in Reschio’s houses are treated to a weekly dressage performance when, Sgr. Conte, who cuts a dashing figure on his white stallion or Antonello, director of the Reschio Stables since 2003, and his stable team, put our powerful horses through delicate and incredible manoeuvres
.
.
We fiercely protect our centuries old wilderness & love to share it. Rent a house or take over Hotel Castello di Reschio before the hotel opens in Spring 2021

node.text:
Reschio’s wilderness hides a font of energy within its Tabaccaia.  For 20 years the creative centre at the heart of the estate, B.B. Architecture & Design Studio unleashes vision and technical know-how to transform a crumbling castle to a superlative hotel, abandoned farmsteads to elegant houses with sweeping gardens, landscapes within natural contours, stylish interiors with picture windows especially for sunset, beautiful furniture & accessories; all designed from the hub that is The Tabaccaia
’From here in the heart of Italy, we are sending love and best wishes for recovery to everyone around the world affected at this difficult time. We will also continue to send scenes from Reschio, which we hope will be cheering, and will remind us of Italy’s unique and enduring beauty.’ #WithlovefromItaly

🔊 Watch the video as our lifelong dream to convert the Castello, our former home, into a family-run hotel becomes a reality. 
It started at the kitchen table in 2001 with sketches and ideas to accommodate family and friends a bit more comfortably than our charmingly robust quarters.  Then, we were further fuelled to create something extraordinary. 
The process has been an incredible journey. Consolidating the work of medieval masons, in restoring the massive stone walls.  Rebuilding every floor and roof, installing hydraulic and electrical systems as well as the most energy-efficient technology available.  Cherry-picking fun and eclectic antique furniture and paintings, then restoring them over a period of four years, to complement and contrast with my new design pieces specially conceived for the Castello. 
The excitement is gigantic, and ever growing. We are raring to open the doors to you in early 2021
———-
From here in the heart of Italy, we are sending love and best wishes for recovery to everyone around the world affected at this difficult time. We will also continue to send scenes from Reschio, which we hope will be cheering, and will remind us of Italy’s unique and enduring beauty #WithlovefromItaly

node.text:
Foraging is an art, purposefully roaming the Reschio Estate, checking on sites to ensure that nature’s store cupboard has a chance to regenerate; collecting all manner of things for medicinal, health or taste purposes. When the foragers return, things are bottled and always named, often an inspiration for still life painting
&
More than 70% of the Reschio Estate is ancient oak and chestnut forests with meadows carpeted in wild flowers where deer, porcupine & wild boar freely roam the countryside
.

Tonight we celebrate la notte di San Lorenzo, when shooting stars scud across the sky making wishes come true.  Where better to gaze at the night sky than an alfresco dinner at the Ristorante Alle Scuderie, where those who own and rent houses on the Reschio Estate come to celebrate & enjoy exquisite dishes & an incredible starscape
&
We work with nature to ensure the authentic taste of ingredients grown in our kitchen garden & replenish Reschio’s larder with foraged foods from the wild
.

node.text:
Conte di Reschio, a previous inhabitant of the castle, watches over those in a Grand Suite affectionately named after him. His initials are embroidered on the bed linen throughout the Hotel Castello di Reschio, after all it was his great uncle, Pope Clemente XII who renewed the title of Conte di Reschio to celebrate his niece, Anna Corsini’s marriage in 1730. Intriguingly he is holding a pen in a gloved hand hopefully to indicate that he is writer rather than poised to sign a document ending his reign over the castle
&
Art@Reschio: with oil paintings, hand blown glass to complete an antique lamp, a Steinway pianoforte & Nic Fiddian-Green’s monumental sculptures throughout the estate; the spirit of Reschio sings with artistic inspiration. Quirky or serious it is a joy to behold and is often to be found where it is least expected
.
